HEADWORD: Folk lore
<hw>Folk" lore`</hw> }</mhw>. <def>Tales, legends, or superstitions long
current among the people; the unwritten literature of a culture, such as
stories, proverbs, riddles and songs.</def>
<rj><au>Trench.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

